            <div><opener><salute><persName ref="pe2111">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Owen</persName></salute></opener>
                
                <p>I received y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> letter in due time but deferred my answer till I had applied to our country men on the 
                    interesting subject. I am sorry to say that I met with universal discouragement not only from them <sic>to</sic> the english I 
                    have seen in a long series of visits I am just <sic>returnd</sic> from. It cannot be expected a single person can support so grand 
                    a scheme. I therefore with reluctance decline what I cannot carry into effect.<note type="editorial">It is possible that Pennant 
                        may be referring here to the interest of the London-Welsh in pursuing the descendants of the twelfth-century prince, Madog ab 
                        Owain Gwynedd in America. See his letter of 2 July 1791 to Pughe, <ref target="1420.xml">1420</ref>; and on the Madogwys, 
                        Gwyn A. Williams, <hi rend="italic">Madoc: The Making of a Myth</hi> (London: Eyre Methuen, 1979).</note> I wish you better 
                    success with y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0705">Dictionary</title></bibl> which is looked for 
                    with impatience. with my best wishes I rest</p>
                
                <closer><salute>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> friend
                </salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                    <dateline><placeName ref="0001">Downing</placeName> May <gap reason="illegible" unit="letters" quantity="1"/>7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1791.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
            
            <div>
                <p><stamp type="frank">FREE P MA 9 91; [<hi rend="italic">handwritten</hi>:] <placeName ref="pl1251">Holywell</placeName> May seventh. 1791.; 
                    No<gap reason="illegible" unit="letters" quantity="2"/>; Free <persName ref="pe0365">L St Asaph</persName> </stamp>
                    <stamp type="handstamp"><placeName ref="pl1251">HOLYWELL</placeName></stamp></p>
                <p><address><addrLine>To<lb/><persName ref="pe2111">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> William Owen<lb/><placeName ref="pl3038">Penton Place</placeName><lb/><placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName></persName>
                    </addrLine></address></p>
            </div>
